What is so special about winter, you ask? Great food, great food, and great food! Well, Mother Dairy's Winter Wonderland has totally upgraded my winter experience! 

I whipped up supper yummy Kunafa Tiramisu for @zingyzest ! The dish turned out tastier than I expected. Want to know how? 

I used the delectable cheese, cream and butter by @motherdairyfreshdelights and the results are mindblowing! The delicious dessert filled with cheese and cream is a treat!

Don't forget to give this recipe a try! 

Ingredients : 

1 cup Mother Dairy  Cheese Spread 
2 tbsp Mother Dairy Cream 
1/4 cup honey 
1/4 tsp orange zest 
1/2 tsp rose water 
8-10 dried Rose petals 
2 tbsp Mother Dairy Butter
1/2 cup roasted Vermicelli 
1/4 cup water 
3 tbsp jaggery 

Method : 

- In a bowl mix together Cheese Spread, Cream, Honey, Orange zest, rose water, and dried rose petals. 
- Once mixed keep aside 
- In a pan heat butter and add roasted vermicelli to it, cook for 5 mins and add water along with jaggery and let it cook till the Jaggery melts 
- Layer the dessert by adding vermicelli and then the cheese cream mixture 
- Garnish with Pistachios

Green Masala Lobster 😍

This one is my Dadi’s recipe, and I absolutely love it. It’s Spicy, Tangy and sooo good, you have to try it ! 

Recipe : 

Green Masala Prawns / lobster 🍤 🦞 

Marination

In a mixing bowl (parath), add:
	•	Prawns or cleaned lobster – 7–8 pieces
	•	Ginger-garlic paste – 1 tablespoon
	•	Turmeric powder – 1 teaspoon
	•	Salt – to taste
	•	Lemon juice – from 1 whole lemon

Mix well and marinate for 20–30 minutes.

Green Masala Paste

(Use a mortar & pestle or grinder)

Grind the following to a smooth paste:
	•	Grated coconut – 1 cup
	•	Fresh coriander – a handful
	•	Mint leaves – a handful
	•	Green chilies – 2 to 3 (adjust to taste)
	•	Garlic cloves – 7 to 8
	•	Ginger – 1 inch piece

Cooking the Prawns
	1.	Heat oil in a pan.
	2.	Add curry leaves and the marinated prawns or lobster.
	3.	Sauté until prawns are just cooked (do not overcook).
	4.	Remove from the pan and set aside.

Preparing the Gravy
	1.	In a kadhai, heat oil and add curry leaves and mustard seeds 
	2.	Add the prepared green masala paste.
	3.	Cook on medium heat until the oil begins to separate.
	4.	Add:
	•	Coriander powder – 1 tbsp 
	•	Water – as needed to adjust gravy consistency
	•	Fish masala – 2 tbsp 
	5.	Bring to a boil, then add the cooked prawns or lobster.
	6.	Stir 1/2 cup coconut milk, 1/2 cup tamarind water
	7.	Simmer gently for a few minutes.

Final Tadka (Tempering)

In a small pan:
	1.	Heat oil.
	2.	Add:
	•	Mustard seeds
	•	2–3 small dried red chilies
	•	Curry leaves
	•	1 tablespoon finely chopped onion
	•	1 teaspoon Kashmiri red chili powder
	3.	Pour this hot tempering into the simmering curry.
	4.	Let it boil for 2–3 minutes before serving.

Serving Suggestions

Serve hot with:
	•	Rice bhakri
	•	Steamed rice
	•	Chapati😋😋

Dak Bungalow Mutton Curry 🔥

Perfect season to make this stunning mutton recipe, it’s very easy but fulll of flavours ♥️

Saree : @myraa_786 

Recipe : 

Dak Bungalow Mutton Curry

1. Marinate the Mutton
In a large bowl, mix:
– 1 kg mutton (large pieces)
- 2 tbsp mustard oil 
- 2 tbsp Green chilli paste 
– 1-1.5 cup thick curd
– 2 tbsp ginger garlic paste
– 2 tbsp Kashmiri red chilli powder
– 1 tsp turmeric
– Salt to taste

⏱️ Set aside for 1 hour.

⸻

2. Fry the Potatoes & Eggs
– Heat 2 tbsp mustard oil in a heavy pot until smoking.
– Fry 4 peeled, half-boiled potatoes until golden.
– Lightly fry 4 hard-boiled eggs. Set both aside.

⸻

3. Sauté the Onion Base
– In the same pot, add 1 cup sliced onions.
– Fry on medium heat until deep golden brown.

⸻

4. Cook the Mutton
– Add the marinated mutton to the onions.
– Sear on high for 5–6 minutes.
– Add a splash of water if needed.
– Cover and cook on low for 40–50 mins until tender.

⸻

5. Make the Masala
Dry roast and grind:
– 4 tbsp coriander seeds
– 1 tbsp cumin
– 1 tsp black pepper
– 1 tsp cloves
– ½ nutmeg
– 1 small cinnamon stick
– 4 green cardamoms
– 2 blades mace
– 5–6 dried Kashmiri red chillies

⸻

6. Final Assembly
– Add ground masala to the cooked mutton. Around 2-3 big tbsp 
– Cook for 5–7 minutes more.
– Add the fried potatoes and eggs.
– Simmer for a few minutes. Adjust salt/water.

⸻

7. Garnish & Serve
– Top with fresh coriander 🌿
– Serve hot with steamed rice or parathas 🍚🔥

Who decided tiramisu always had to be about coffee?

This World Gin Day, we’re rewriting the rules - with a dessert that’s as refined as it is refreshing: Lemon Gin Tiramisu, made with the beautifully balanced Roku Gin 🍋

Instead of espresso-soaked ladyfingers, think sponge soaked in gin and lemon syrup.
Instead of heavy mascarpone, think airy layers with hints of botanicals.

Honestly? Tiramisu pairs beautifully with Roku. With its six Japanese botanicals - like yuzu peel, sakura flower, and sencha tea, Roku adds a citrusy, floral depth that transforms this classic Italian dessert into something bright, modern, and delightful.

Here’s to celebrating World Gin Day the way it should be with dessert that’s got a little zing, a little class, and a lot of character.
